#healper function to search unique value from list 
def uniqueValueFromList(list_input):
    unique_list_temp = []
    list_set = set(list_input)
    unique_list = (list(list_set))
    for x in unique_list:
        unique_list_temp.append(x)
        # print("unique_list ",x)
    # print("unique_list_temp: ", unique_list_temp)
    # print("len(unique_list_temp): ",len(unique_list_temp))
    return unique_list_temp

#Numerical features analysis
def plot_dis_number (df_list):
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, hue = "Churn", aspect = 2.5, palette={1:"lightgreen", 0:"lightblue"})
    g = g.map(sns.kdeplot,df_list, shade = True, alpha = 0.8 )
    g.set(xlim = (0, data[df_list].max()))
    g.add_legend()
    g.set_axis_labels(df_list, "proportion")
    plt.show()

#PCA analysis

X = data_wo_id_wo_churn = data_without_id.drop(labels = ["Churn"],axis = 1)
Y = data["Churn"].values
# print(X.head())
# print(Y)

# Create Train & Test Data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=101)

sc = StandardScaler()
X_train_std = sc.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_std = sc.transform(X_test)

mean_vec = np.mean(X_train_std, axis=0)
cov_mat = (X_train_std - mean_vec).T.dot((X_train_std - mean_vec)) / (X_train_std.shape[0]-1)
print('Covariance matrix \n%s' %cov_mat)
eigen_vals, eigen_vecs = np.linalg.eig(cov_mat)
print('\nEigenvalues \n%s' % eigen_vals)

# sns.set()
# sns.set_context("talk")
tot = sum(eigen_vals)
print("tot ", tot)
var_exp = [(i / tot) for i in sorted(eigen_vals, reverse=True)]
print("var_exp ", var_exp)
cum_var_exp = np.cumsum(var_exp)

t = np.arange(0, 110, 10)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))
# ax.plot(lstm_fpr, lstm_tpr, linestyle='--', color='r',  lw=2.0, label='LSTM')
# ax.plot(no_fpr, no_tpr, marker='.', color='g', lw=2.0, label='No skill')

ax.bar(range(0, 19), var_exp, alpha=0.5, align='center', color='r', label='individual explained variance')
ax.step(range(0, 19), cum_var_exp, where='mid',  color='r', label='cumulative explained variance')
plt.xlabel('Principal components', fontsize = 18)
plt.ylabel('Explained variance ratio', fontsize = 18)
plt.title('PCA', fontsize = 18)
plt.legend(loc='best',fontsize = 18)
ax.grid(True)
ticklines = ax.get_xticklines() + ax.get_yticklines()
gridlines = ax.get_xgridlines()
ticklabels = ax.get_xticklabels() + ax.get_yticklabels()

#Single LSTM Model
# Create Train & Test Data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=101)
print(X_train.shape, y_train.shape, X_test.shape, y_test.shape)
print(X_train)

X_train = X_train.values
X_test = X_test.values

print(X_train.shape, y_train.shape, X_test.shape, y_test.shape)

X_train = X_train.reshape((X_train.shape[0], 1, X_train.shape[1]))
X_test = X_test.reshape((X_test.shape[0], 1, X_test.shape[1]))

print(X_train.shape, y_train.shape, X_test.shape, y_test.shape)

# design network
model_lstm = Sequential()
print("X_train.shape[0] ", X_train.shape[0])
# model.add(LSTM(50, input_shape=(X_train.shape[1])))
model_lstm.add(LSTM(50, input_shape=(X_train.shape[1],X_train.shape[2])))
model_lstm.add(Dense(1))
model_lstm.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
# fit network
history = model_lstm.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=72, validation_data=(X_test, y_test), verbose=2, shuffle=False)
# history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_data=(X_test, y_test), verbose=2, shuffle=False)

#Output display
training_loss = history.history['loss']
print("Training Loss :", training_loss)

validation_loss = history.history['val_loss']
print("Validation Loss :", validation_loss)


# ScoreTrain = np.array(history.history['loss'])
# print("ScoreTrain",ScoreTrain)
# ScoreTrain1 = (100.0-ScoreTrain)
# print("ScoreTrain1 ", ScoreTrain1)


t = np.arange(0, 110, 10)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
ax.plot( training_loss, color='r',  lw=2.0, label='Training loss')
ax.plot(validation_loss, color='g', lw=2.0, label='Validation loss')
plt.ylabel('Loss', fontsize = 18)
plt.xlabel('Epochs', fontsize = 18)
plt.legend(loc='best',fontsize = 18)
ax.grid(True)
ticklines = ax.get_xticklines() + ax.get_yticklines()
gridlines = ax.get_xgridlines()
ticklabels = ax.get_xticklabels() + ax.get_yticklabels()

for line in ticklines:
    line.set_linewidth(3)

for line in gridlines:
    line.set_linestyle('-')

for line in gridlines:
    line.set_linestyle('-')

for label in ticklabels:
    label.set_color('black')
    label.set_fontsize('large')

plt.show()

# LSTM Model Evaluation
yhat = model_lstm.predict(X_test)
X_test = X_test.reshape((X_test.shape[0], X_test.shape[2]))

final_yhat =yhat
final_yhat_list = []
ii = 0
for yhat_val in final_yhat:
    if yhat_val[0] >= 0.5:
        final_yhat_list.append(1)
    else:
        final_yhat_list.append(0)
    ii+=1
    
    
# print("final_yhat_list len :", len(final_yhat_list))

print ("Accuracy LSTM ",metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, final_yhat_list))

# calculate RMSE
rmse_new = sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, final_yhat_list))
print('Test RMSE: %.3f' % rmse_new)

confmat = confusion_matrix(y_true=y_test, y_pred=final_yhat_list)
print("Confusion Matrix New:")
print(confmat)

labels = ['Not Churned', 'Churned']
plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))
ax= plt.subplot()
sns.heatmap(confmat,cmap="Reds",annot=True,fmt='.1f', ax = ax); 
# labels, title and ticks
ax.set_xticklabels(labels)
ax.set_yticklabels(labels)
ax.set_xlabel('Predicted labels');ax.set_ylabel('True labels'); 
ax.set_title('Confusion Matrix LSTM');


confmat_nor = confmat.astype('float') / confmat.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]
labels = ['Not Churned', 'Churned']
plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))
ax= plt.subplot()
sns.heatmap(confmat_nor,cmap="Greens", annot=True,fmt='.1f', ax = ax); 
# labels, title and ticks
ax.set_xticklabels(labels)
ax.set_yticklabels(labels)
ax.set_xlabel('Predicted labels');ax.set_ylabel('True labels'); 
ax.set_title('Normalized Confusion Matrix LSTM');

ax.plot(lstm_fpr, lstm_tpr, linestyle='--', color='r',  lw=2.0, label='LSTM')
ax.plot(fpr_knn, tpr_knn, linestyle='--', color='b',  lw=2.0, label='KNN')
ax.plot(fpr_lr, tpr_lr, linestyle='--', color='y',  lw=2.0, label='LR')
ax.plot(fpr_dt, tpr_dt, linestyle='--', color='c',  lw=2.0, label='D-Tree')
ax.plot(fpr_rf, tpr_rf, linestyle='--', color='m',  lw=2.0, label='RF')

ax.plot(no_fpr, no_tpr, marker='.', color='g', lw=2.0, label='No skill')

plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate', fontsize = 18)

#Saved Model Execution 
def read_and_predict(test_data):
        # load model
        f = open('Telco_LR.pickle', 'rb')
        model = pk.load(f); f.close();       
        predicted_Churned     = model.predict(test_data)
        print ("predicted_Churned ", predicted_Churned)
        confmat_out = confusion_matrix(y_true=y_test, y_pred=predicted_Churned)
        print("Confution Matrix:")
        print(confmat_out)
        
        df = pd.DataFrame(predicted_Churned, columns =['predicted_Churned']) 
        df.to_csv('FinalResult.csv', index = False)
